						               													<description>Q-Memory is a game where your memory is the only asset to fix the quantum link. With 18 hexagonal tiles, game modes that bring more challenging experiences and a 5-10 minute duration which makes this game the perfect filler game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On their turn, players will try to finish the quantum link (which means revealing all of the tiles) but in order to do so, they need to follow the quantic sequence.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each time a player flips up a hex-tile, it will have to connect with the previously revealed tile either on it&amp;acute;s core colour(black or white) or the background color. If they match, then the next tile revealed must match the opposite(if it matched the core, now it has to match the background color and vice versa). If, at any time, the conditions are not met, the player must flip back down all the tiles and the next player starts their turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to finish the quantum link will be the winner of Q-Memory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
